,p_plug_source=>wwv_flow_string.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'<img src="#APP_IMAGES#tip.png">',
'<h2>On the Master Node &P14_HOST_NAME. </h2>',
'<ul>',
'',
'  	<li> <b> Step-1: Swarm init </b>',
'	<br> <code> <span style="background-color:#D2CFCE;">sudo docker swarm init --advertise-addr `hostname -i` </span> </code> ',
'	<br>',
'	You would see a swarm join token something like below. Copy that ',
'	<br>',
'	<code><span style="background-color:#DAF7A6;">docker swarm join --token SWMTKN-1-1rdn6x5tnqosuaveu9hknkal7eh38pp9ehh8hltjuvm94ffbjt-cem86auiihln1o23jflqg8tbs 10.40.158.90:2377 </span></code>',
'	<br>',
'		In case you want to retrieve the above token, you can run below command on the master node',
'		<code><span style="background-color:#D2CFCE;">sudo docker swarm join-token manager </span></code>',
'	</li>',
'	<li> <b> Step-2: Create Swarm Overlay Network <span style="background-color:#FFC300;"> &P14_NETWORK_NAME. ',
'</span> </b> <br>',
'		<code><span style="background-color:#D2CFCE;">sudo docker network create --driver overlay --subnet=10.10.0.0/16 &P14_NETWORK_NAME. --attachable <span></code>',
'	</li>',
'	<li> <b> Step-3: Mount JAPAC Shared file folder </b> <br>',
'		<code><span style="background-color:#D2CFCE;">sudo mkdir -p /scratch/share/japac-file-share-mnt',
'sudo mount -o ro fsgbu-mum-128.snbomprshared1.gbucdsint02bom.oraclevcn.com:/scratch/share/japac-file-share /scratch/share/japac-file-share-mnt </span></code>',
'	</li>',
'</ul>',
'',
'<h2>On Worker Node(s) </h2>',
'On each worker node, please execute the below steps.',
'<ul>',
'  	<li> <b> Step-1 Swarm Join </b>',
'	<br> Paste the swarm join command copied from master node. E.g.:',
'	<code><span style="background-color:#D2CFCE;">sudo docker swarm join --token SWMTKN-1-1rdn6x5tnqosuaveu9hknkal7eh38pp9ehh8hltjuvm94ffbjt-cem86auiihln1o23jflqg8tbs 10.40.158.90:2377 </span></code>',
'	</li>',
'		',
'	<li> <b> Step-2: Mount JAPAC Shared file folder </b> <br>',
'		<code><span style="background-color:#D2CFCE;">sudo mkdir -p /scratch/share/japac-file-share-mnt',
'sudo mount -o ro fsgbu-mum-128.snbomprshared1.gbucdsint02bom.oraclevcn.com:/scratch/share/japac-file-share /scratch/share/japac-file-share-mnt </span></code>',
'	</li>',
'</ul>',
'<br>',
'<h3> Label Your nodes! </h3>',
'Workloads created by Swarm will be distributed randomly across the available nodes in the cluster.',
'<br>',
'You may need to label the nodes so that the services will be distributed accordingly',
'<ul>',
'<li>',
'Label the DB node(s) with "nodetype==db" <br>',
'<span style="background-color:#D2CFCE;"><code> docker node update --label-add nodetype=db <i>worker-node-name</i> </code></span>',
'</li>',
'<li>',
'Create DB Volume and Log folder in DB Node<br>',
'<span style="background-color:#D2CFCE;"><code> mkdir -m777 -p /scratch/share/plato/{environment identifier}/db /scratch/share/plato/{environment identifier}/db/logs </code></span>',
'</li>',
'<li>',
'For the nodes that you want OBMA App Workload, label the node with "nodetype==obma-app".',
'<span style="background-color:#D2CFCE;"><code> docker node update --label-add nodetype=obma-app <i>worker-node-name</i> </code></span>',
'</li>',
'<li>',
'Label the other App Nodes label it with appropriate selector. E.g. "nodetype==fcubs-app" <br>',
'<span style="background-color:#D2CFCE;"><code> docker node update --label-add nodetype=fcubs-app <i>worker-node-name</i> </code></span>',
